Program: Outlook
Title: 03/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00g94py
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 4 May 2011
Personal stories of the violence and terror inspired by Osama Bin Laden. We hear from Julie Nicholson a vicar who lost her faith after her daughter died in the London bombings and Vinny Camaj, the son of Roco Camaj a window cleaner who died working at the Twin Towers. Also, bereaved mother Talat Hamdani whose son, Mohammed Salman Hamdani, was falsely suspected of perpetrating the September 11 attacks and Ashraf al-Khaled, whose father and in-laws were killed at his wedding party in Jordan. Show less